# Uncle pre-night hang-out (drinking) dialogue.
# Format: see data/dialogue/school.dlg. One line = one page (click to advance).
#
# UncleHangout.gd picks one of the three [open_*] sections at random, then plays
# [closing]. There is no long/lore version yet — see the TODO in
# UncleHangout._start(). When you write it, add a [long] section here and branch
# on it in that script the first time (GameState.uncle_hangout_seen).

[open_1]
Uncle: Hey Kid, have a drink with me.

[open_2]
You hear a clinking come from the kitchen. Looking over, you see it's your uncle.
Uncle: Hey Kid, have a few beers with me.

[open_3]
You see your uncle opening up a bottle of whiskey.
Uncle: Get over here kid, have some with me.

[closing]
You both talk for a while... He drinks quite a bit.
Uncle: That's it, I'm callin' it a night.
He stands and stumbles in place.
Uncle: I'm exhausted... Seeya Kid.
Thoughts: He'll be out like a light for sure. I won't have to worry about him checking on me tonight.
